Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Yosemite National Park
Description: America's "oldest" national park. It only became a national park after Yellowstone because national parks didn't exist when it was set aside.

Name: Pinnacles National Park
Description: It used to be a national monument, until Obama made it a national park. Thanks, Obama!

Name: The Palace of Fine Arts
Description: Originally built for the 1915 Panama–Pacific Exposition in San Francisco. It's a very pretty building with nothing inside.

Name: Sather Tower
Description: I'm sorry Storke Tower, but your older brother is much prettier. The third-tallest bell-and-clock tower in the world!

Name: Pier 39
Description: Popular San Francisco tourist attraction; large sea lion population.

Name: 17-Mile Drive
Description: A pleasant scenic road in Pebble Beach. Has a lot of golf courses.
